  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAndroid 15 is here, and there are plenty of ways this year\u0026#39;s update is \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/why-android-15-better-than-android-14/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebetter than Android 14\u003c/a\u003e. Now that owners of Android phones, from the largest to \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-small-phones/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethe smallest phones\u003c/a\u003e, are starting to get the Android 15 upgrade, we can\u0026#39;t help but look ahead to Android 16. In our review of Android 15, it was clear that the best new features weren\u0026#39;t the flashiest. Still, some of my favorite feature additions and changes found in Android 15 could use some work. Let\u0026#39;s review three things Google added in Android 15 but should change in Android 16.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"4135-4f10-b379c2256dff\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n                    \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/android-15-review/\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/10/android-15-icon-hero-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n       